article.description: Courtney Williams scored 12 points to lead a balanced attack as No. 12 Texas A&M overwhelmed Hawaii 82-41 on Friday night.
article.headline: No. 18 Texas A&M women roll past Hawaii 82-41
article.linkText: No. 18 Texas A&M women roll past Hawaii 82-41
article.story:
LAIE, Hawaii --  Courtney Williams scored 12 points to lead a balanced attack as No. 12 Texas A&M overwhelmed Hawaii 82-41 on Friday night.

Khaalia Hillsman, Courtney Walker and Rachel Mitchell had 10 points apiece as all 12 players scored for the Aggies (6-1).

Kalei Adolpho had 10 points for the Rainbow Wahines (4-5), who shot 33 percent, missed all 10 of their 3-pointers and had 21 turnovers.

Texas A&M, which led 39-15 at halftime, shot 55 percent, making 3 of 4 behind the arc, and had just four turnovers.
